The paper deals with the dynamics of multi-agent networks, which is a topic covered in the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses algebraic graph theory, which falls under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of its results for the operation and design of multi-agent systems, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
